      "references": "[EKS89] Erd\\H{o}s, P. and Kro\\'o, A. and Szabados, J., On convergent interpolatory polynomials. J. Approx. Theory (1989), 232--241.",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s, Kro\\'{o}, and Szabados \\cite{EKS89} proved that, if $\\epsilon>0$ is fixed and does not $\\to 0$, then there exist sequences $x_{ij}$ such that, for any continuous function $f$, there exists a sequence of polynomials $p_n$, with degrees $\\deg p_n<(1+\\epsilon)n$, such that $p_n(x_{kn})=f(x_{kn})$ for all $1\\leq k\\leq n$, and $p_n(x)\\to f(x)$ uniformly for all $x\\in [-1,1]$."
    },
